#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:21
msgid "Storing an AIP"
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:23
msgid "1. Once ingest is complete, selecting a location to \"Store AIP\" in the Actions drop-down menu compresses and zips the AIP and moves it into Archival storage."
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:26
msgid "2. In the demo version of Archivematica the AIP storage directory is ``/sharedDirectoryStructure/www/AIPsStore/``. In other environments it can be a remote network mounted directory. If multiple AIP storage locations have been created in the Storage Service, each will appear in the Store AIP location dropdown, including LOCKSS locations."
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:33
msgid "3. The AIP directories are broken down into UUID quad directories for efficient storage and retrieval."
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:38
msgid "UUID quad directories: Some file systems limit the number of items allowed in a directory, Archivematica uses a directory tree structure to store AIPs. The tree is based on the AIP UUIDs. The UUID is broken down into manageable 4 character pieces, or \"UUID quads\", each quad representing a directory. The first four characters (UUID quad) of the AIP UUID will compose a sub directory of the AIP storage. The second UUID quad will be the name of a sub directory of the first, and so on and so forth, until the last four characters (last UUID Quad) create the leaf of the AIP store directory tree, and the AIP with that UUID resides in that directory.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:48
msgid "4. The Archival storage tab in the Archivematica dashboard consists of a table with information about the stored AIPs. Use the up and down arrows in the column headers to sort by AIP name, size, UUID, date stored or status. Note that at the top of the table is the total size of the stored AIPs and the number of indexed files."
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:59
msgid "5. To open a copy of the AIP, click on the AIP name. You can then open or download the zipped AIP."
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:62
msgid "6. The AIP pointer file can be accessed by clicking on the Pointer file link. The pointer file provides information on the AIP and its relationships to the Archivematica, DIPs, and other AIPs as appropriate."
msgstr ""

