msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:80
msgid "The index includes the AIP names and METS contents."
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:81
msgid "Search results show AIPs and AIP parts with their UUIDs and the ability to click on the raw ElasticSearch file and view it in another screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:89
msgid "Note that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:91
msgid "All METS metadata is indexed and searchable."
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:93
msgid "Use the first dropdown menu to search in: File UUID, File path, File extension, AIP UUID, and AIP name"
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:95
msgid "Use the second dropdown menu to search by keyword or phrase"
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:96
msgid "Click in the box next to the Show files? box to include files in your results"
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:98
msgid "Clicking on search results allows for local download of the entire AIP. Clicking on a file will result in opening the file if your browser has a viewer, or downloading it if your browser does not."
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:102
msgid "By clicking on \"View raw\" next to a search result, you can also view the raw JSON data that contains the METS data, the Archivematica version that generated the data, the AIP UUID, the time indexing occurred, and the relative file path within the AIP."
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:110
msgid "Deleting an AIP"
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:112
msgid "1. To request AIP deletion, click on the red delete icon next the AIP in the Archival storage tab table."
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:121
msgid "Archivematica will ask for a reason for deletion."
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:128
msgid "Choosing to delete an AIP will send a request to your Archival Storage Service administrator. If the administrator approves the request, your AIP will be deleted from your Archival Storage and your index will be updated. If the administrator denies the request, the AIP will remain in storage and your administrator should contact you."
msgstr ""

#: ../user-manual/archival-storage/archival-storage.rst:136
msgid "Note that Archivematica tracks the location and existence of AIPs in 2 ways, within the Storage Service and in the Elastic Search index which you can search via the dashboard. Deleting AIP's directly from the file system rather than through the Storage Service will cause inconsistencies in both applications and is not recommended in a production environment."
msgstr ""

